summary: Dr. B. M. Inamdar, a Gynaecologist of repute, is endeavoring to take his organisation - Datt Maternity & Surgical Home, at a higher level of competence, modern technological assimilation & committed service to mankind through unique blend of dynamism, enterprise development, social responsibility and transparency. He has been at the forefront of numerous accomplishments since his childhood. He was a national scholar, got numerous prizes and awards in the school, including 'First in Sanskrit' in suburbs of Mumbai. He was 9th in the medical merit list and was easily admitted in Seth G. S. Medical College of KEM Hospital. He continued his meritorious career in Medical College. He passed his M.B.B.S. in first class. Subsequently he did his M.D. in Obstetrics and Gynaecology from KEM Hospital. He passed M.D. Examination from Bombay University with distinction.    During his MD, he worked in KEM Hospital, Cooper Hospital and Sion Hospital, where he acquired his surgical skills under direct training of many of the stalwarts like Dr. Purandare, Dr. Chaubal, Dr. Vaidya and Dr. Sathe. He joined Datt Maternity & Surgical Home. Being interested in Endoscopic work, he added Endoscopic Instruments and started helping the community by doing minimally invasive surgeries. In 1994 & 1995, he went to Bielefeld (Germany) and Kiel University, Germany. In Kiel University, he was trained by Professor Kurt Semm, who is known as "Father of Gynecological Endoscopic Surgery". He earned his diploma in Pelviscopic surgery from Kiel University, Germany. In 1987, he joined Yeshwant Hospital and Charitable Trust, Kandivali as honorary Gynaecologist. He added and developed endoscopic department in Yeshwant Hospital and was one of the popular Gynaecologists in the area. At present, he is managing Datt Maternity & Surgical Home with lot of experience & skills in Obstetrics & Gynaecology. The patients know him for his humane approach and as one who is ever ready to assist needy patients as and when required. He is also a visiting gynecologist for “Cloud Nine Hospital” and “SRV Hospital” in Goregaon. He loves to teach and is invited to deliver lectures at various Medical and Non-Medical Fora. He has given number of lectures in Indian Medical Association, Rotary and other Public Fora. He has conducted numerous Medical Camps under the aegis of Rotary Club of Mumbai West Coast. He is a prominent Rotarian having received numerous awards in Rotary. He has been a District Governor in 2012-13, looking after R. I. District - 3140 that includes the whole of Mumbai and Thane, spreading upto Dahanu, Kulgaon, Ulhasnagar and Navi Mumbai. As a Governor, he could undertake many paathbreaking projects like “Pediatric Heart Surgeries”, Maternal Mortality Reduction in Jawhar etc In Rotary, he is considered as dedicated and committed Rotarian having hitech skills. In social life, he was a Government's Special Executive Officer in 2000. He founded "Doctors Against Sex Determination and female foeticide" and was instrumental in bringing Maharashtra Act against Sex Determination and Female Foeticide. Government of Maharashtra appointed him as Technical Advisor for the above Act. He was elected in various Medical Bodies. He has been President of Indian Medical Association - Mumbai West Branch - in the year 2009-10. He was adjudged as the “Best President in all 2000 branches of IMA”. He has also been Vice President of IMA Mumbai West Branch & Maharashtra State Branch for the year 2007-2008. He was a convenor of the Annual Conference of Association of Medical Consultants. He has been State Executive and Central Council Member of IMA for many years. Recognizing his skills, Johnson and Johnson gave him an Appreciation Award for "enriching quality of life for women through innovative healthcare solutions" - in 2002. He is also an avid sportsman and loves playing Cricket and Chess. He has organized and won numerous tournaments. He has been President of Medicos Chess Federation. Also, he was Vice-President of Mumbai Suburban District Table Tennis Association. He was Chairman, Central Council, Medicos Cricket in 1994. Dr B.M.Inamdar's intention is to provide the basic as well as most modern Health care facilities to the residents of the locality at an affordable price. Quality assurance with personalized attention has been the goal of Dr B.M. Inamdar and the staff of Datt Maternity and Surgical Home.  He firmly believes that: Never give wrong guidance to patients for financial gains. Always do ethical work “Quality Health care treatment & Transparency in dealing” is his motto. Treat all class of patients with equal care.

summary: Practice: New Delhi/Mumbai MD (Obgyn, Mumbai University), DNB, FCPS, DGO, MS (Stanford University), IUGA International Fellowship in Urogynecology & Pelvic Reconstructive Surgery, Cleveland Clinic Florida Founding Director of the upcoming Tata Center for Urogynecology & Pelvic Health, Cama Hospital, Mumbai Founder & Director, C.U.P (Center for Urogynecology & Pelvic Health), New Delhi  Consultant Urogynecologist, Global Hospital, Mumbai Member, Editorial Board, International Urogynecology Journal Member, Publications Committee, IUGA (International Urogynecological Association) Member, International Urogynecology Committee, an august body of world-renowned experts constituted to create practice guidelines for prolapse.  Founder, Chairperson & Managing Trustee, ARMMAN (NGO)   The Center for Urogynecology & Pelvic Health team in New Delhi includes the founder Director Dr. Aparna Hegde & Associate Consultant, Dr. Karishma Thariani, who holds fellowship degree in Urogynecology from AIIMS. Dr. Karishma Thariani is available from 9 am 7 pm, Monday to Saturday in Delhi.    Detailed bio: Dr. Hegde is India's leading Urogynecologist & Pelvic Reconstructive Surgeon. She holds MD, DNB, FCPS (Gold Medal) & DGO degrees (ObGyn) & MS (Stanford University). She was awarded the IUGA (International Urogynecology Association) International Fellowship in Urogynecology & Pelvic Reconstructive Surgery which she completed in the prestigious department of Urogynecology at Cleveland Clinic Florida before returning to India. In addition to her private practice, she is also the founding Director of the upcoming Tata Center for Urogynecology & Pelvic Health, India’s first comprehensive academic clinical ‘Center of Excellence’ in the field.   A National Talent Search Scholar, Dr. Hegde has had a sterling academic career with numerous distinctions through her medical training & the best resident award. An accomplished researcher, she is an internationally recognized pioneer in the field of 2D & 3D ultrasound of the pelvic floor & is routinely invited as an expert to national & international conferences including IUGA & AUGS (American Urogynecology Society) annual meetings to conduct round tables & workshops. She has multiple national & international research awards including a best paper award at the 2013 American Urogynecological Society (AUGS) Annual meeting, best poster award from Cleveland Clinic Florida, three young scientist awards from FOGSI (Federation of Obstetrics & Gynecological Societies of India) & MOGS (Mumbai Obstetrics & Gynecological Society) & numerous best paper awards in FOGSI conferences. She has more than 74 abstracts & publications in peer-reviewed national & international journals. She has been invited by the Sri Lankan Gynecology Society, Malaysian Urogynaecological Society & the Canadian Gynecology Society to conduct seminars & workshops on her research work. The protocols created by her in imaging of slings are now being implemented in various US & Canadian Universities. She was invited to give the mini-state-of-the-art lecture on her research work at the IUGA conference in Capetown (2016) & as faculty to the FIGO conference in Brazil (2018).  Dr. Hegde is also the Founder & Managing Trustee of ARMMAN, an NGO that leverages technology innovatively to create scalable, evidence-based programs in the field of maternal & child health in 16 states. ARMMAN’s five programs have reached across to more than 1.9 million women & their children to date.  ARMMAN is implementing the largest mhealth program in the world, Kilkari in a public private partnership with health ministry, Government of India in 13 states.  She is a Tedx speaker & she was awarded USAID ‘Social Entrepreneur’ award (2018), ‘Woman ChangeMaker’ award (Womanity Foundation, Geneva, 2017), Woman Icon Award in Asia (2016), ), the Mother Teresa Social Leadership Fellowship (2016), Digital Woman Entrepreneur Award (2015), Top Social Innovator Award (2014 & 2017, the Ganatra award for social work by MOGS ( 2013), the Prerak fellowship by IIM Lucknow (2014), ‘People’s Choice Award’ at Saving Lives at Birth event (Washington DC, 2011) etc. She has been featured as one of the five global women leaders in the Voice of America documentary, ‘A Single Step: Journeys of Women Leaders’ (2015). ARMMAN was awarded the British Medical Journal S. Asia Award for ‘Maternal & Child Health Team’ (2018), WHO Public Health Champion Award (2017), the Public Health Initiative of the year award (2017), the silver award at the Indian Digital Awards (2017) & is the only Indian NGO to have won the ‘GSK-Save the Children International’ Health Innovation award (2017 (one of four awardees out of 170 applications from 40 countries). She was chosen by Harvard University from NGO leaders from all over the world to attend the SNP program in 2016 & invited by Harvard Business School & Harvard Kennedy School to speak in the social impact panel in the Harvard India Conference in February 2017.

summary: Dr.Minal Davay is a passionate and dedicated Obstetrician and Gynaecologist, committed to providing comprehensive women's healthcare services. With years of experience and extensive medical training, she has dedicated her career to supporting women in their reproductive health journey. Her goal is to create a comfortable and safe environment where patients can openly discuss their concerns and receive personalized care.  Education and Credentials: She completed her MBBS from MVP Medical College, Nashik, and subsequently pursued a specialization in Obstetrics and Gynaecology at MAHARASHRA UNIVERSITY OF HEALTH SCIENCES(MUHS),Nashik. Additionally, she constantly update her knowledge and skills through continuing medical education to stay at the forefront of advancements in the field.  Professional Experience: Over the years, she has had the privilege of working in various prestigious medical institutions,  like SURYA MATERNITY AND CHILD CARE HOSPITAL, HBT BMC HOSPITAL,etc where she has gained invaluable experience in diagnosing and treating a wide range of gynecological conditions. her clinical expertise spans from routine gynecological check-ups and family planning to complex reproductive surgeries and fertility treatments.  Approach to Patient Care: she firmly believe in patient-centered care, and she strive to build strong doctor-patient relationships based on trust and empathy. Her approach is holistic, taking into account not just the physical health but also the emotional and mental well-being of her patients. she actively listen to their concerns, respect their choices, and involve them in the decision-making process to ensure the best possible outcomes.  Areas of Specialization:  Her special interests lie in various areas of gynecology, including but not limited to:  1. Obstetrics: Prenatal care, childbirth, and postnatal care. 2. Gynaecological Disorders: Management of menstrual irregularities, pelvic pain, and urinary problems. 3. Reproductive Health: Family planning, contraception counseling, and fertility assessments. 4. Gynaecological Surgeries: Minimally invasive procedures, laparoscopic surgeries, and hysteroscopy. 5. Menopause Management: Addressing the challenges and symptoms associated with menopause.  Patient Education: Education is a vital part of her practice. She is committed to empowering her patients with accurate and up-to-date information regarding their health. Through clear communication and education, she aim to help her patients make informed decisions about their well-being.  Community Involvement: In addition to her clinical practice, she actively participate in community health programs and awareness campaigns. she believe in the importance of educating the public about women's health issues and promoting preventive measures. summary: Dr Hrishikesh Pai had done MD, FCPS, FICOG, MSc, is one of the country’s leading gynecologist. He is the present Secretary General of the Federation of Obstetric and Gynaecological Societies of India (FOGSI). Previously, Dr Pai was the Senior Vice President of FOGSI in 2006. Dr Pai is also the pioneer in the field of Infertility and IVF since 1991. He is the Director of the Bloom IVF Group which runs nine IVF centres all over India including Lilavati hospital & Bhatia Hospital, Mumbai and Fortis Hospitals in New Delhi, Gurgaon, Faridabad, Noida, Mohali and Navi Mumbai. He has been the first doctor in India to introduce numerous innovations in medical fields such as assisted laser hatching, spindle view, ovarian tissue freezing for cancer patients, oocyte freezing, IMSI and embryoscope. In appreciation of his enormous contributions, the international agency Frost & Sullivan bestowed upon him the best IVF group in India award in 2013. In appreciation of his work Dr. Pai has got elected as the Member – Board of Directors of the World body of Infertility namely International Federation of Fertility Societies (IFFS): a first for an Indian. His clinical interests are as follows: Infertility therapy & Family planning Operative Laparoscopy & Hysteroscopy Endovaginal Sonography
